columns.name: version
columns.description: The version of the Lambda function.

columns.name: function_name
columns.description: The name of the function.

columns.name: arn
columns.description: The function's Amazon Resource Name (ARN).

columns.name: master_arn
columns.description: For Lambda@Edge functions, the ARN of the master function.

columns.name: state
columns.description: The current state of the function.

columns.name: code_sha_256
columns.description: The SHA256 hash of the function's deployment package.

columns.name: code_size
columns.description: The size of the function's deployment package, in bytes.

columns.name: description
columns.description: The function's description.

columns.name: handler
columns.description: The function that Lambda calls to begin executing your function.

columns.name: last_modified
columns.description: The date and time that the function was last updated, in ISO-8601 format.

columns.name: last_update_status
columns.description: The status of the last update that was performed on the function.

columns.name: last_update_status_reason
columns.description: The reason for the last update that was performed on the function.

columns.name: last_update_status_reason_code
columns.description: The reason code for the last update that was performed on the function.

columns.name: memory_size
columns.description: The memory that's allocated to the function.

columns.name: revision_id
columns.description: The latest updated revision of the function or alias.

columns.name: runtime
columns.description: The runtime environment for the Lambda function.

columns.name: timeout
columns.description: The amount of time in seconds that Lambda allows a function to run before stopping it.

columns.name: vpc_id
columns.description: The ID of the VPC.

columns.name: kms_key_arn
columns.description: The KMS key that's used to encrypt the function's environment variables.

columns.name: role
columns.description: The function's execution role.

columns.name: signing_job_arn
columns.description: The ARN of the signing job.

columns.name: signing_profile_version_arn
columns.description: The ARN of the signing profile version.

columns.name: state_reason
columns.description: The reason for the function's current state.

columns.name: state_reason_code
columns.description: The reason code for the function's current state.

columns.name: ephemeral_storage_size
columns.description: The size of the function's /tmp directory in MB.

columns.name: environment_variables
columns.description: The environment variables that are accessible from function code during execution.

columns.name: policy
columns.description: Contains the resource-based policy.

columns.name: policy_std
columns.description: Contains the contents of the resource-based policy in a canonical form for easier searching.

columns.name: vpc_security_group_ids
columns.description: A list of VPC security groups IDs attached to Lambda function.

columns.name: vpc_subnet_ids
columns.description: A list of VPC subnet IDs attached to Lambda function.

columns.name: architectures
columns.description: The instruction set architecture that the function supports.

columns.name: dead_letter_config
columns.description: The function's dead letter queue configuration.

columns.name: file_system_configs
columns.description: Connection settings for an Amazon EFS file system.

columns.name: image_config_response
columns.description: The function's image configuration values.

columns.name: layers
columns.description: The function's layers.

columns.name: logging_config
columns.description: The function's Amazon CloudWatch Logs configuration settings.

columns.name: runtime_version_config
columns.description: The ARN of the runtime and any errors that occurred.

columns.name: snap_start
columns.description: Configuration for creating a snapshot of the initialized execution environment.

columns.name: tracing_config
columns.description: The function's X-Ray tracing configuration.
